From: Leo Chen <leochen@broadcom.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Mar 2010 19:39:24 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 27/47] backport: use cpumask_of_cpu instead of cpumask_of

use cpumask_of_cpu to replace cpumask_of in core.c

Signed-off-by: Leo Hao Chen <leochen@broadcom.com>
Integrated-by: Fei Wu <fei.wu@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm/mach-bcmring/core.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/mach-bcmring/core.c b/arch/arm/mach-bcmring/core.c
index 492c649..335e04c 100644
--- a/arch/arm/mach-bcmring/core.c
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-bcmring/core.c
@@ -358,7 +358,7 @@ void __init bcmring_init_timer(void)
 	timer0_clockevent.min_delta_ns =
 	    clockevent_delta2ns(0xf, &timer0_clockevent);
 
-	timer0_clockevent.cpumask = cpumask_of(0);
+	timer0_clockevent.cpumask = cpumask_of_cpu(0);
 	clockevents_register_device(&timer0_clockevent);
 }
 
